  "buggy_files": ["sound/pci/hda/hda_intel.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["azx_resume"],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The bug is in azx_resume function. When an audio timeout/error occurs (in azx_rirb_get_response), error recovery code sets chip->single_cmd=1, chip->polling_mode=1, and increments chip->poll_count. However, these error recovery flags are never reset during the suspend/resume cycle. When azx_resume is called and subsequently calls azx_init_chip, the function checks 'if (!chip->single_cmd)' at line 1222-1223 and skips the azx_init_cmd_io call (which reinitializes CORB/RIRB). This leaves the controller in single_cmd mode, which is slow and causes choppy audio. The fix requires resetting these flags to their initial values in azx_resume before calling azx_init_chip: chip->single_cmd=0, chip->polling_mode=0, chip->poll_count=0."
}

